{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Job’s Honor Turned to Contempt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“But now they mock me, men younger than I am, whose fathers I would have refusedto entrust with my sheep dogs."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "What use to me was the strength of their hands, since their vigor had left them?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Gaunt from poverty and hunger, they gnawed the dry land,\nand the desolate wasteland by night."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They plucked mallow among the shrubs, and the roots of the broom tree were their food."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They were banished from among men, shouted down like thieves,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so that they lived on the slopes of the wadis, among the rocks and in holes in the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They cried out among the shrubs and huddled beneath the nettles."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A senseless and nameless brood, they were driven off the land."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And now they mock me in song; I have become a byword among them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They abhor me and keep far from me; they do not hesitate to spit in my face."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Because God has unstrung my bow and afflicted me, they have cast off restraint in my presence."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The rabble arises at my right; they lay snares for my feet\nand build siege ramps against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They tear up my path; they profit from my destruction,\nwith no one to restrain them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They advance as through a wide breach; through the ruins they keep rolling in."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Job’s Prosperity Becomes Calamity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Terrors are turned loose against me; they drive away my dignity as by the wind,\nand my prosperity has passed like a cloud."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And now my soul is poured out within me; days of affliction grip me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Night pierces my bones, and my gnawing pains never rest."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "With great force He grasps my garment; He seizes me by the collar of my tunic."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He throws me into the mud, and I have become like dust and ashes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I cry out to You for help, but You do not answer; when I st and up, You merely look at me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have ruthlessly turned on me; You oppose me with Your strong hand."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You snatch me up into the wind and drive me before it;\nYou toss me about in the storm."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Yes, I know that You will bring me down to death, to the place appointed for all the living."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Yet no one stretches out his hand to a ruined manwhen he cries for help in his distress."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Have I not wept for those in trouble? Has my soul not grieved for the needy?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But when I hoped for good, evil came; when I looked for light, darkness fell."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I am churning within and cannot rest; days of affliction confront me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I go about blackened, but not by the sun. I st and up in the assembly and cry for help."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have become a brother of jackals, a companion of ostriches."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My skin grows black and peels, and my bones burn with fever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My harp is tuned to mourning and my flute to the sound of weeping."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}